1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,560
- Do you want to try dating me, Mr. Trai?
- Huh?

2
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,360
You asked Mr. Trai to be your boyfriend?!

3
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,440
Yeah.

4
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,360
I'm giving you my body.

5
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:50,720
Then I'll be your gift too.

6
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,440
I want her to hurt.

7
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,160
It'd be even better if she just died.

8
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:04,440
Rachen!

9
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,600
Please take care of Rachen for me, okay?

10
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,800
<i>You're Mr. Trai's girlfriend.</i>

11
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,520
How could he tell you
to care for another man?

12
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,360
You two are not
just friends anymore, are you?

13
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:14,440
If Mr. Trai
really steps aside for Mr. Rachen…

14
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,760
I've got someone to take care of me.

15
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:18,360
- Here I am. I'm here.
- Pakbung?

16
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:20,760
Trai told me he won't take
anything from me anymore.

17
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,240
That probably includes you.

18
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:24,840
But I'm not anyone else. I'm…

19
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:26,120
You're what?

20
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:29,720
One day, you'll get hurt, like I did.

21
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:39,720
I've prepared a warm bath for you already.

22
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:51,480
It's okay.

23
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,560
You sure you can bathe by yourself?

24
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,320
And if I can't, will you help me?

25
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:00,480
There'd be an extra charge.

26
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:02,480
150,000 to bathe you.

27
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,320
500,000 for me to go into the tub.

28
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,960
That's more like the Pakbung I know.

29
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:12,240
When you came in,
you looked really irritated.

30
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:18,040
I am irritated.

31
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:23,000
But I have to separate
work from personal matters.

32
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:27,120
Very good. I like this version of you.

33
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,800
Focused on money, cheerful,

34
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,360
being yourself,

35
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,680
not tying your happiness
or suffering to anyone.

36
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,240
Right.

37
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,960
Tying it only to money is already good.

38
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:51,200
Thank you.

39
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,480
Rachen, are you…

40
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,880
Pakbung. You bitch.

41
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,080
- Mika.
- Hey.

42
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,920
Mika, Mika, let go.

43
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,680
Let go!

44
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,200
- Mika.
- So you came

45
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:15,360
all the way here to seduce him?

46
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:16,720
Mika, let her go.

47
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:18,240
I said let go.

48
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:21,160
You said you were badly injured.
How could you even sleep with her?

49
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:24,680
Your mind's always in the gutter.
No one stoops as low as you do.

50
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,560
You come in and start insulting people.
Are you crazy?

51
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:30,080
You psycho! That hurts!

52
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,760
- Hey!
- You hurt me too.

53
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:35,000
Wanna see whose scalp is tougher?

54
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:35,960
Huh?!

55
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:38,000
You wanna try me?

56
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:39,920
I've got hands and feet too, you know!

57
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,360
Pakbung, stop!

58
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:44,320
- You crazy bitch!
- Pakbung! Darin, help stop them. Now.

59
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,600
I can't. I'm scared.

60
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,840
Then go get Trai. Hurry.

61
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:50,600
Trai, hurry!

62
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:51,560
Hey, Pakbung.

63
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,000
- Stop!
- Pakbung, stop.

64
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:54,440
- Stop!
- Let go!

65
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,280
- Stop!
- Let go!

66
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:58,440
- Stop, Pakbung.
- You're ganging up?

67
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:00,640
You're ganging up on me? I'll tell my mom.

68
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,720
You're good at running to your mom.

69
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,160
You suck at fighting
but are great at running to mommy?

70
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,360
I said stop!

71
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,760
She started it!

72
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,080
Pakbung, I said stop!

73
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:13,240
Mika, there's nothing
between me and Pakbung.

74
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,000
She's just here to care for me
as an employee.

75
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:18,000
‪Rachen, why?
‪Why are you protecting her again?

76
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:20,520
- You've already slept with her, right?
- Mika.

77
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,840
Listen to me. Calm down and listen to me!

78
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:28,040
I'm the one who asked Pakbung
to take care of Rachen myself.

79
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,520
There's nothing to be jealous about.

80
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:32,720
And Rachen would never
cross the line with Pakbung

81
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,520
because Pakbung is my girlfriend.

82
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:41,720
And if you have a problem with Pakbung,

83
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,560
then you have a problem with me too.

84
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,040
- And what are you gonna do about it?
- Wanna try me?

85
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,840
Wait. Where are you going?

86
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,480
You're really going
to let Pakbung go home alone?

87
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:21,280
She just had a fight with Mika.
Her mother won't let this go.

88
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,520
I already had Prarop
take her home and keep watch over her.

89
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:27,440
Prarop alone isn't enough.
I'm going myself.

90
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,640
You're not fully recovered, are you?

91
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:35,200
So you're more worried about my feelings

92
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,280
than your own girlfriend's?

93
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:44,160
Pakbung already told me she's dating you.

94
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:45,960
But you didn't tell me

95
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:50,840
because you were afraid
of hurting my feelings.

96
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:54,640
You're willing to sacrifice for me,
but you don't care about Pakbung at all?

97
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,800
I…

98
00:07:56,880 --> 00:08:00,360
You can't take care of Pakbung,
just like you couldn't take care of Dad.

99
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:02,920
You can't take care of anyone, Trai.

100
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:08,880
So, step aside. I'll handle it myself.

101
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:17,000
I never intended
to let go of Pakbung for you.

102
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:20,840
Didn't you tell me you wouldn't take
anything from me ever again?

103
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:22,760
Have you forgotten?

104
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,480
I haven't.

105
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,440
But I'm not taking anything,

106
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,560
because Pakbung was never yours.

107
00:08:35,559 --> 00:08:37,400
Go rest until you're better.

108
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:40,679
About my relationship,
I'll take care of it myself.

109
00:08:56,560 --> 00:08:59,240
What a shame I wasn't there yesterday.

110
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:01,040
I could've helped you pull
that rich girl's hair.

111
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,040
So what did Mr. Trai say?

112
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:09,840
Nothing. He just had
Mr. Prarop take me home.

113
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:10,760
We didn't even talk.

114
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:15,120
You got beaten up like that,
and he didn't even comfort you?

115
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,960
Comfort me? He only scolded me more,

116
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,200
like I was the one who started it.

117
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,920
He's probably worried about you.

118
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,800
But of all people,
you had to get into it with Mika.

119
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:30,080
You know how scary her mother is, right?

120
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,600
After this,

121
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:35,000
Mrs. Mookmanee
definitely won't let you off easy.

122
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:41,680
I'm screwed. What have I done?

123
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:44,600
Ugh, realizing it now is too late.

124
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,480
Hey, don't be scared.

125
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,200
She probably
won't send someone to kill us…

126
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,560
I guess.

127
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:01,840
Oh, my.

128
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:02,920
Weapons? Weapons.

129
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,560
Oh, what's that sound?

130
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,520
- Hey, take it.
- Okay.

131
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,800
Take it.

132
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:15,760
Yeah.

133
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,640
Go.

134
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:23,560
What?!

135
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:26,120
What is this?
Are you rehearsing for a performance?

136
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,080
Shooting content?

137
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:30,240
What content?
These are weapons for self-defense.

138
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:31,360
Yeah.

139
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:34,960
We're afraid Mrs. Mookmanee
might send someone to hurt Pakbung.

140
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:37,200
No way. I stayed on watch all night.

141
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,120
No suspicious people at all.

142
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,160
Why are you here?

143
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,200
To clear things up.

144
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:46,800
- Wait. She's not saying okay yet.
- Okay.

145
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:51,320
I want to talk to Mr. Trai alone.

146
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,400
Do you want to talk first, or should I?

147
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:18,400
You came here, so you start.

148
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,680
I'm sorry.

149
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:30,840
I'm sorry for yelling at you
when you fought with Mika.

150
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:35,000
I'm sorry for being hesitant
about our status in front of Darin.

151
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:38,360
And I'm sorry for making it look like
I was handing you over to Rachen.

152
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:40,200
I'm truly sorry about the last part.

153
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,920
I cared too much about Rachen's feelings,

154
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,920
and I forgot about yours.

155
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:51,960
Can you forgive me?

156
00:11:57,120 --> 00:12:00,000
10 baht's worth of gold
and I'll stop being mad at you.

157
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,280
Pakbung.

158
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,840
Can you be serious for once?

159
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:07,480
I don't want to be serious.
Being serious hurts.

160
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:11,560
Pakbung…

161
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,840
Yesterday, I didn't like myself.

162
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,520
I couldn't control anything,

163
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,240
like my emotions depended on what you did.

164
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:25,080
I felt awful.

165
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,640
Even if I'm not mad at you anymore today,

166
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:32,280
if being with you makes me
dislike myself again,

167
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:35,080
then I think we should reconsider
our relationship status.

168
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,520
See? I told you.

169
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,120
I don't want to be serious.

170
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,520
Pakbung.

171
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:50,480
Thank you for being honest with me.

172
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:53,000
I understand you better now.

173
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:55,320
I won't make you feel bad again.

174
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,200
Give me a chance, Pakbung.

175
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:07,720
POINT-COLLECTING CARD

176
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,520
A point-collecting card?

177
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,400
Yes.

178
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,040
Whenever I do something good for you,

179
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:16,440
or you make me happy,

180
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,760
I'll put one of these stickers

181
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,520
in this box.

182
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,040
When it reaches ten stars,

183
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:25,240
there's a grand prize,
whatever you want to ask for.

184
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:28,640
Anything at all?

185
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:31,320
And if I make you angry

186
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:33,160
or you make me sad,

187
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,880
then we put one of these,

188
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,880
an angry-faced sticker.

189
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,680
You already made me upset.

190
00:13:42,760 --> 00:13:44,360
But I'm not counting this time.

191
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,960
But if there's a next time,

192
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:50,800
I'll keep adding them
until it reaches ten, and then…

193
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:52,400
Don't you dare say we'll break up.

194
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,480
You'll have to pay me as your apology.

195
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,520
Fine.

196
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,320
Then I'll pay you with…

197
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,720
my heart.

198
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,760
What am I, some ghoul?

199
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,080
Keep your heart.

200
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,400
I want money.

201
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:18,280
Money. Money. Money. And money.

202
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,120
Got it?

203
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:22,680
- Money?
- Yes.

204
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,760
Hey, hey!

205
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,960
What are you doing?
Why are you carrying me?

206
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,560
You want money?

207
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:38,600
Then I'll pay you with… my body.

208
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:44,040
Hey.

209
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:46,800
Hey! Get off me.

210
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:49,240
You want me to put
an angry-face sticker or what?

211
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,560
I want a star sticker from you more.

212
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:10,000
Thank you for understanding me.

213
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,920
It's not like I wanted
to break up with you.

214
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,720
How could I?
I still haven't gotten a single baht.

215
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,120
Pakbung…

216
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,400
It's true.

217
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:29,400
So money is all you care about, huh?
Money, huh?

218
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,520
- Pakbung, huh?
- Hey.

219
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,320
- Huh?
- You wanna fight?

220
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:35,880
- You only care about money?
- No.

221
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,120
That's not it.

222
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,640
Should we invite monks
to perform a big merit-making ceremony?

223
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,160
Something bad always happens here.

224
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:04,520
It's totally déjà vu.

225
00:16:07,080 --> 00:16:09,400
How many times will we have
to clean this place up before we can open?

226
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:12,400
Ugh, you're not even old yet.
Stop complaining.

227
00:16:13,800 --> 00:16:16,000
I'm not complaining. I'm just saying.

228
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:17,000
Yes?

229
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:18,400
I didn't call you.

230
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,200
Come help lift this table.

231
00:16:21,280 --> 00:16:24,440
You complain too much.
You can't lift it alone?

232
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:34,520
Mr. Trai.

233
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:36,400
Yes?

234
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:38,840
Whose phone is this?

235
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,280
That's Rachen's.

236
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,640
How many phones does Mr. Rachen have?

237
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:49,040
Just this one.

238
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,680
But when he was in the hospital, he said
it was broken, so I bought him a new one.

239
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:58,200
I couldn't contact Mr. Rachen all night,
so I tracked his phone signal.

240
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:02,640
If Mr. Rachen only has one phone,
which is this one,

241
00:17:04,839 --> 00:17:08,480
then how could he say that day
that he tracked Mr. Rachen's phone

242
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,800
and found him at the hospital?

243
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,119
Wait. Who are you talking about?

244
00:17:15,880 --> 00:17:17,000
Rut.

245
00:17:23,599 --> 00:17:25,359
Mr. Rachen, you're feeling better now?

246
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:29,320
I tried to visit you so many times,
but Mr. Trai wouldn't let me in.

247
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,200
I'm better now.

248
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:42,800
Were there any updates while I was away?

249
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:46,120
I investigated the stock
buying and selling like you asked.

250
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:48,320
I found a list of suspects.

251
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:52,200
I'm still digging into
whether it connects to Mrs. Mookmanee.

252
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,840
Is that why you got shot?

253
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,080
It's possible.

254
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:01,840
The police are investigating.

255
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:04,760
The police still
haven't identified the shooter?

256
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:19,120
How long have you been
working for me, Rut?

257
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:23,400
Next month will be three years.

258
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:25,400
Three years already?

259
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,600
Time flies.

260
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,000
We're together almost every day,

261
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:36,400
yet I don't know anything about you.

262
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:57,360
If you're free tonight,
let's go out to eat.

263
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,000
I want to get to know you better.

264
00:19:53,680 --> 00:19:55,720
What do you need me for, Mrs. Mookmanee?

265
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:58,400
I remember you are Rachen's secretary.

266
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:00,360
I didn't care…

267
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,480
until I found out you were more than that.

268
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:10,120
I'm not sure what you mean.

269
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,640
Even if you destroyed the safe house
you were hiding in,

270
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:15,120
my people still tracked you down.

271
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:17,880
Doing everything alone all this time…

272
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:20,560
you're pretty skilled.

273
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,240
I have work to do.

274
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:26,000
If there's nothing else, please excuse me.

275
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:28,360
I want to support you, Rut.

276
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,120
Someone as capable as you

277
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,040
could go much further with a sponsor.

278
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,240
You want to hire me?

279
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,280
Name your price.

280
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,680
Money is not a big deal for me.

281
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:50,880
Thank you for the offer,
but you've misunderstood.

282
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:55,240
I'm not doing this for money.

283
00:21:02,640 --> 00:21:04,080
Not for money?

284
00:21:24,520 --> 00:21:26,480
So you're suspicious of me too, Trai?

285
00:21:41,360 --> 00:21:44,440
Pakbung picked a fight with me.
She crossed the line again.

286
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:48,000
You said you'd help me.
You haven't done anything at all.

287
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:50,240
I called you, and you didn't even pick up.

288
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:53,080
If you're not actually going to help,
don't come offering yourself.

289
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,560
Hey! Stop rambling already!

290
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:57,960
You…

291
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:02,240
I'm sorry.
I've been under a lot of stress lately.

292
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:05,720
Ever since Mr. Rachen got shot,
everything's been chaotic.

293
00:22:05,800 --> 00:22:06,760
I'm really sorry.

294
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:12,520
I'm sorry as well
for taking it out on you.

295
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:14,280
As for Pakbung,

296
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:18,800
I'm going to deal with her for you.
I just haven't found the right timing yet.

297
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:26,320
But if you help me,
it might make things easier.

298
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:29,920
How?

299
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:36,720
They're holding the event
at two branches at the same time.

300
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:39,280
- Yes.
- For the Bangna branch,

301
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:43,600
they only want staff,
so I'll send Niuniu and Samlee there.

302
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:47,480
For the Bang Yai branch,

303
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:50,680
they need an event organizer
and someone to run the cue,

304
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:52,680
so I was thinking I'd go with Pakbung.

305
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,840
So we have to split up, Petch?

306
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:02,760
Mr. Trai hired us to stay with Pakbung
all the time, you know.

307
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,040
I understand that.

308
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:12,920
But honestly,
my schedule's been light lately,

309
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:16,480
so when this job came in,
I had to take it.

310
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:20,120
If it weren't so last-minute,

311
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:22,560
I wouldn't bother you guys at all.

312
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:28,160
Bother us? Come on.

313
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:29,880
Don't forget.

314
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:33,880
I'm your company's partner too.

315
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,560
Your work is basically my money.

316
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,480
Of course, I'll do it.

317
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:46,840
You might not know this,
but your secretary

318
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:48,760
forged all
of his job application documents.

319
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:52,640
No one seems to be living at that address.

320
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:55,240
So I checked his educational background
with the university.

321
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:58,680
No one named Rut
graduated in the year he claimed.

322
00:23:58,760 --> 00:24:00,920
As for his past employers,

323
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,280
they admitted they were hired
to lie for him.

324
00:24:03,360 --> 00:24:06,920
From what I suspected, the culprit
must be extremely skilled in IT.

325
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:11,080
But I didn't think he'd be good enough to
fake records and identities this cleanly.

326
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:14,520
So you think Rut is the culprit.

327
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:18,760
Even if he doesn't have a scar on his
wrist, he's the most suspicious one now.

328
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:24,920
That day, I only saw the attacker's eyes,
so I wasn't sure.

329
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:28,640
Yesterday,
I tried inviting Rut out to talk,

330
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:31,040
but he didn't show up.

331
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:32,320
That's when I started to think it's him.

332
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:35,920
Do you know where Rut is right now?

333
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:42,600
Thanks.

334
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:50,160
You really think you can protect her?

335
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:09,400
WE DIDN'T FINISH IT LAST TIME.

336
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:11,320
GOT THE GUTS TO FACE ME YOURSELF?

337
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:14,000
OR ARE YOU ONLY GOOD AT HIDING
UNDER YOUR MOM'S SKIRT?

338
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:18,080
Pakbung.

339
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:21,160
IF YOU'RE THAT TOUGH, COME MEET ME.

340
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:23,080
You're challenging me?

341
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,040
We're here.

342
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:48,920
Are you sure this is the place, Petch?

343
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:53,360
This isn't a closed restaurant,

344
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,480
it's just an abandoned hotel.

345
00:25:56,080 --> 00:26:00,440
Uh… but this is where the pin shows.

346
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:04,240
Let me call the client again.

347
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:11,120
<i>Sorry, the number you have dialed</i>
<i>cannot be reached at this time.</i>

348
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,280
I can't get through.

349
00:26:14,960 --> 00:26:18,080
I think this isn't the place.
We should leave.

350
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,600
Yeah, let's go.

351
00:26:21,960 --> 00:26:22,960
Let's go.

352
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:29,800
Pakbung.

353
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:30,800
Ms. Mika?

354
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:34,040
Hey!

355
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:37,160
So you lured me here just to slap me?
You're still not done?

356
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:40,520
Yeah, I'm not done. You were the one
who texted and challenged me.

357
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:41,880
How dare you?

358
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:45,240
You rotten pakbung.

359
00:26:45,320 --> 00:26:47,400
- Stop, please.
- Hey.

360
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:51,400
- Petch, take Pakbung and run!
- Pakbung, go.

361
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,040
- Pakbung, go.
- Let go of me!

362
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:54,480
- Let's go.
- Pakbung!

363
00:26:54,560 --> 00:26:55,520
Hurry up.

364
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,200
Pakbung, watch out!

365
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:02,480
Pakbung!

366
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:04,880
Pakbung! Follow her!

367
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,280
Come on.

368
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:15,280
Pakbung, where are you? Pakbung!

369
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:20,560
Pakbung!

370
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:32,120
Mr. Rut?

371
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,200
Mr. Rachen asked me
to come take care of you.

372
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,240
This way, please.

373
00:27:45,280 --> 00:27:46,640
My car is parked just up ahead.

374
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:03,760
Pakbung, what's wrong?

375
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:13,240
My stomach hurts, Petch.

376
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:17,160
Oh, what should we do?
Want me to carry you on my back?

377
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,280
I can just pick you up. Come on.

378
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:33,360
Mr. Rut.

379
00:28:33,440 --> 00:28:35,280
My stomach hurts. I really can't walk.

380
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:37,760
Can you go get the car
and pick us up here?

381
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:43,360
Stop bullshitting, Pakbung.

382
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:46,680
Why would you talk like that?

383
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,840
Petch!

384
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:59,280
Hey. Pakbung…

385
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,640
- Pakbung.
- Petch!

386
00:29:08,320 --> 00:29:10,120
Petch, hang in there.

387
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,960
Hello. Someone's been shot.

388
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:18,680
Mr. Trai, Prarop's calling.

389
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,360
Pakbung…

390
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,160
What?

391
00:29:35,520 --> 00:29:36,760
Pakbung.

392
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,160
Mr. Trai.

393
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:57,680
You shot Petch.

394
00:29:58,760 --> 00:30:01,480
What do you want? Why did you shoot him?!

395
00:30:03,960 --> 00:30:05,440
He was in the way.

396
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:15,280
Mr. Rachen would never order
something like this.

397
00:30:16,520 --> 00:30:18,240
Mrs. Mookmanee hired you, didn't she?

398
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:24,680
Do you think everyone in this world
is money-hungry like you, Pakbung?!

399
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,120
Then what do you want?

400
00:30:29,520 --> 00:30:31,280
You've been trying
to kill Mr. Trai all along.

401
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:35,160
Mika said I sent her those messages,

402
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:36,600
but I didn't send anything!

403
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:38,240
That was you, wasn't it?!

404
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:42,720
You planned everything, didn't you?

405
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:47,000
Don't tell me you kidnapped me
to use me as bait

406
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:48,840
and lure Trai here.

407
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:52,080
Wow, so damn smart.

408
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:54,680
Too bad
you figured it out a little too late.

409
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,560
What did Mr. Trai ever do to you?

410
00:30:57,640 --> 00:31:01,080
Figure it out yourself.
Think, think, think.

411
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:07,120
He hurt you, didn't he?
That's why you hate him this much.

412
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:10,840
Stop asking so many damn questions!
You're annoying the hell out of me!

413
00:31:15,320 --> 00:31:18,080
I don't want to die. I'm scared.

414
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,920
Poor you…

415
00:31:20,600 --> 00:31:22,400
There, there.

416
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:25,120
Don't be scared.
Mr. Trai will come save you.

417
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:26,360
He'll come save you.

418
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:29,320
You already called him?

419
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:32,280
Not yet. Why rush it?

420
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:37,560
Let him suffer,
search for you for a day or two.

421
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:39,080
Then I'll call him. Sounds good?

422
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:41,160
Good?

423
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:44,080
Does that sound good? Sounds good?

424
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:49,160
You psychopath.

425
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:55,400
This is nothing compared to what Trai
and Tritot did to me. Remember that.

426
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:58,480
You're cunning. I shouldn't let you live.

427
00:32:01,160 --> 00:32:02,080
Damn it!

428
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:02,960
Pakbung!

429
00:32:03,040 --> 00:32:04,760
You just love sticking your nose
where it doesn't belong.

430
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:07,040
If you'd stayed out of it,
you wouldn't have to die.

431
00:32:07,120 --> 00:32:11,080
But you had to get involved with Trai.
You were in my way.

432
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:20,960
Even if you die, I can still use
your corpse to lure Trai here.

433
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:22,320
Right?

434
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:27,600
Hey!

435
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:33,280
Mr. Trai.

436
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:38,360
I've set your phone
to share your location with mine.

437
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:40,160
And here.

438
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:42,560
I saved my number
as your emergency contact.

439
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,240
If anything happens, press this button.

440
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:47,040
Your phone will immediately
send an SOS message to me.

441
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,960
My stomach hurts, Petch.

442
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:51,400
Oh, what should we do?

443
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:52,880
Want me to carry you on my back?

444
00:32:57,480 --> 00:33:00,120
It's him. He's the attacker.
He's going to kill you!

445
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:02,680
I know. I know.
I'm here now. I'm here to help.

446
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:04,240
Don't be scared, Pakbung.

447
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:37,560
Lee!

448
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,000
Come here!

449
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:45,880
Pakbung.

450
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:47,840
Pakbung.

451
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:55,760
What do you want? What did I ever do?
Why did you kill my father?

452
00:33:55,840 --> 00:33:57,600
You're the one who killed my parents.

453
00:33:57,680 --> 00:34:00,080
What the hell are you talking about?
When did I ever kill them?

454
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:02,800
When you got drunk and drove, Trai.
Don't you remember?

455
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:05,840
My dad was the scapegoat
who went to jail for you.

456
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,320
You're Uncle Rat's son?

457
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:13,600
Don't. Don't.

458
00:34:13,679 --> 00:34:15,040
Don't!

459
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,920
No.

460
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:20,760
If you hate me or are angry at me,
then take it out on me alone!

461
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:23,600
Don't play hero.
All of you are going to die.

462
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:25,960
Lee and Pakbung have nothing
to do with this. Let them go.

463
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:27,719
Why?

464
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:29,920
You can't stand seeing the people you love

465
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,040
get hurt?!

466
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:33,440
And what about me?!

467
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:36,280
I had to watch the people I loved die!
How do you think I felt?!

468
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:41,239
My mom died because of your money.

469
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:45,239
When my dad found out,
he wasted away in prison and died.

470
00:34:45,320 --> 00:34:48,679
You people are selfish to the core.

471
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:50,280
Whoever lives or dies, you never care.

472
00:34:54,920 --> 00:34:57,360
It's still hot, Son. Here.

473
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,280
Thank you, Dad.

474
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:02,280
And this too.

475
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,680
- Your favorite shrimp paste dip.
- Thank you, Mom.

476
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:08,280
You two should eat too.
You keep serving me everything.

477
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:11,640
Eat a lot. Exams are coming up.
You'll need energy to study.

478
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:12,480
Yes, Mom.

479
00:35:12,560 --> 00:35:16,360
I'll save a big meal
for the day you graduate.

480
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:20,600
You're gonna be so hungry.

481
00:35:20,680 --> 00:35:21,800
It won't be long.

482
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:24,200
Our Rut is smart.

483
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:26,680
I couldn't afford
to send you to a good school,

484
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:29,200
but you worked hard
and earned a scholarship yourself.

485
00:35:29,280 --> 00:35:32,280
If all I can do is pick the meat
off the fish for you, why wouldn't I?

486
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:39,280
Then I'll graduate quickly and find a job,
so you both can finally live comfortably.

487
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:42,960
My parents weren't rich,

488
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,680
but they never let me suffer.

489
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:50,040
When I was with them, I was so happy.

490
00:35:51,320 --> 00:35:54,440
But then my dad got a new job,
driving for your father.

491
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:58,680
The pay was higher.
It looked like life would get better,

492
00:35:59,280 --> 00:36:01,360
but it didn't!

493
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:19,360
Rut, your dad's calling.

494
00:36:22,560 --> 00:36:23,480
Yes, Dad?

495
00:36:24,080 --> 00:36:26,880
<i>Go to bed first, Rut. Don't wait for me.</i>

496
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,920
<i>Tonight, I don't think I can come home.</i>

497
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:33,560
But Dad, you said you'd eat with me
on my graduation day.

498
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:37,640
<i>I want to celebrate with you,</i>
<i>but what can I do?</i>

499
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:39,840
<i>Mr. Tritot is still working.</i>

500
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:41,520
<i>If the boss isn't done,</i>

501
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:43,960
<i>how can I go home first?</i>

502
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:46,040
<i>I have to go now, Son.</i>

503
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:51,760
On an important day my dad had waited for,
he couldn't come because of your father.

504
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:53,680
Your father worked him morning to night.

505
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:55,840
Why?!

506
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:59,960
Why do you think just because you're rich
that you're above everyone else?

507
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:02,240
You're just rich.

508
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:06,080
You think you can order anyone to die
or go to prison for you? Bastard!

509
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:10,760
You know, my family was my only happiness.

510
00:37:10,840 --> 00:37:13,240
And you,
you and your father took that from me.

511
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:16,360
Who gave you the right?! Who gave you
the right to destroy my happiness?

512
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:19,880
Rut, it's my fault. I admit it, all of it.
Just let everyone go.

513
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,840
No! Don't show your face now.

514
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:24,360
It's too late.
I don't want anything from you.

515
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:26,360
But I'll make you understand that

516
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:29,840
even if I'm not rich or have money
like you, I can still destroy your life.

517
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:32,960
I'm going to kill everyone you love.

518
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:35,480
Don't, Rut. No. Don't. Rut.

519
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:37,880
Don't! Don't, Rut!

520
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:39,080
Don't!

521
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:41,560
Pakbung.

522
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:51,480
Someone's injured here.

523
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:14,080
Why did you kill my father, you bastard?!

524
00:38:16,120 --> 00:38:18,560
Why did you kill my father?!
You piece of shit!

525
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:20,880
You scum! Why did you do that?!

526
00:38:21,640 --> 00:38:24,520
Why, Rut?! Why did you do that?!

527
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:26,720
Why did you kill my father?

528
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:31,000
Why did you kill my father?

529
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:38,600
You bastard! Let go of me!

530
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,360
Please calm down.

531
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,640
- Please calm down.
- Let go!

532
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:45,600
Let go!

533
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,360
Please don't blame yourself, Mr. Trai.

534
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:56,800
Everything is all my fault.

535
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:19,680
How could I be so stupid?
He was right by my side all along,

536
00:39:21,120 --> 00:39:22,760
and I never once suspected him.

537
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:30,960
You're okay, right?

538
00:39:35,240 --> 00:39:36,680
I thought the attacker

539
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,920
was someone who hated Be Rich
or Dad's business.

540
00:39:41,800 --> 00:39:44,240
But all of this was because of me.

541
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:50,120
Uncle Rat worked for Dad for years,
but we never really knew his family.

542
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:53,880
Just like Rut.

543
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,640
He worked for me for so long,

544
00:39:57,840 --> 00:39:59,320
yet I never really knew him either.

545
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:03,040
If anyone is to blame, it's all of us.

546
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,680
Aren't you going to blame me at all?

547
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:09,280
I'm the reason…

548
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:13,520
that Dad died.

549
00:40:17,720 --> 00:40:20,240
You're already falling apart
just by blaming yourself, right?

550
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:24,760
When you're better, then I'll blame you.

551
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,600
Go take care of Pakbung.

552
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,200
She's waiting for you.

553
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:16,880
Please wait here for a moment.

554
00:41:16,960 --> 00:41:17,920
Okay.

555
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:24,040
Don't you want to stay overnight
for observation?

556
00:41:25,120 --> 00:41:26,680
I'm really not that badly hurt.

557
00:41:27,720 --> 00:41:30,280
The nurse said I can rest at home.

558
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:38,440
‪Sit down.

559
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,800
How are Petch and Mr. Lee?

560
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:44,680
Petch lost a lot of blood,
but we got him to the hospital in time.

561
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:47,320
He's safe now. As for Lee,

562
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,720
the bullet missed any critical organs.

563
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:50,560
A few days of rest and he'll be fine.

564
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:57,000
Prarop, please look after Lee for me.

565
00:41:57,880 --> 00:41:59,040
Of course.

566
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:04,320
I'm sorry, Pakbung.

567
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:07,520
You got hurt because of me again.

568
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,320
You weren't the one who hurt me.

569
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:32,520
- Let it be!
- Let it be!

570
00:42:34,720 --> 00:42:35,560
Here.

571
00:42:38,800 --> 00:42:39,760
Om.

572
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:40,840
Bad luck, be gone.

573
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:44,440
Spirit, come back. Spirit, come home.
May all your suffering and sorrow be gone.

574
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:49,920
He's going to get worse
because of your ritual.

575
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:53,720
Don't jinx it!

576
00:42:53,800 --> 00:42:56,320
These are star gooseberry leaves
and soap pods.

577
00:42:56,400 --> 00:42:58,800
Tradition says they ward off evil spirits.

578
00:42:58,880 --> 00:43:01,520
And this is holy water from nine temples.

579
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:03,920
Honestly, he's supposed to bathe in it.

580
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:06,200
Yeah, and you should too.

581
00:43:08,880 --> 00:43:09,720
Come on.

582
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:11,800
What if it infects the wound?

583
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:14,360
Right. Good point.

584
00:43:16,040 --> 00:43:17,800
Then, let's do a fake sprinkle for now.

585
00:43:17,880 --> 00:43:18,720
Om…

586
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:20,600
Let it be!

587
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:22,280
Let it be!

588
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:27,040
Don't make me laugh.
My stitches will split.

589
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:31,720
Does it still hurt?

590
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:33,960
On and off.

591
00:43:37,720 --> 00:43:39,280
Don't make that face.

592
00:43:40,560 --> 00:43:43,640
I'm actually glad we survived.

593
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:47,360
Let's say we paid off some bad karma.

594
00:43:48,120 --> 00:43:51,120
From now on,
only good things should come our way.

595
00:43:52,840 --> 00:43:54,160
In that case,

596
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:58,360
you should buy lottery tickets this draw.
You'll win for sure.

597
00:43:58,440 --> 00:43:59,440
Yeah.

598
00:43:59,520 --> 00:44:00,640
Yeah…

599
00:44:01,240 --> 00:44:03,680
Does that mean you have lucky numbers?

600
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:05,400
No.

601
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:08,600
It's just that earlier today,
the police came to question me.

602
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:10,520
They asked

603
00:44:10,600 --> 00:44:14,160
who contacted me
about the job at the restaurant.

604
00:44:17,080 --> 00:44:18,440
Wasn't it Mr. Rut?

605
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:22,760
But the caller was a woman.

606
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:27,160
Her name was… Rujee.

607
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:30,160
When the police

608
00:44:30,240 --> 00:44:32,000
traced the number,

609
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:35,440
they said no such person existed.

610
00:44:36,760 --> 00:44:38,240
Rujee…

611
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:40,960
Rut… Oh?

612
00:44:41,040 --> 00:44:42,520
Those names are similar.

613
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:45,200
Could they be siblings?

614
00:44:47,400 --> 00:44:49,920
Or could it have been Ms. Mika's voice?

615
00:44:50,560 --> 00:44:52,040
No.

616
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:55,040
The voice sounded older.

617
00:44:56,720 --> 00:44:57,880
Then who was that?

618
00:45:05,600 --> 00:45:09,720
Mom, how was I supposed to know
that Rut was the son of that driver?

619
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:14,520
Oh, he was planning to kill Trai too.

620
00:45:18,560 --> 00:45:22,280
How would I know? I shouldn't have called
to tell you this at all.

621
00:45:23,320 --> 00:45:24,760
I already said I didn't know.

622
00:45:24,840 --> 00:45:27,360
I don't know, I don't know,
I don't know anything.

623
00:45:35,680 --> 00:45:38,320
Use this new SIM
to call and hire Pakbung for the job.

624
00:45:40,480 --> 00:45:41,600
I…

625
00:45:41,680 --> 00:45:45,880
I'll tell you exactly what to say.
Trust me.

626
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:47,840
No one will know it was you.

627
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:01,240
RUT

628
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:02,240
DELETE

629
00:46:02,320 --> 00:46:03,160
MOVE TO TRASH

630
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:15,520
Darin.

631
00:46:17,480 --> 00:46:18,680
Darin.

632
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:32,880
Did you know Rut's been arrested?

633
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:39,320
Rut? Your secretary? Arrested for what?

634
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:41,200
How close are you to Rut?

635
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:45,960
I only know him as your secretary.

636
00:46:46,560 --> 00:46:48,080
But you called him more often than I did.

637
00:46:48,680 --> 00:46:50,160
And only your number is in his phone.

638
00:46:51,920 --> 00:46:55,200
He was hitting on me. But I wasn't
interested. I just felt sorry for him.

639
00:46:55,800 --> 00:46:56,960
Felt sorry?

640
00:46:57,560 --> 00:46:59,520
So you called
and tricked Petch into that job?

641
00:47:00,160 --> 00:47:01,800
Tricked? What are you talking about?

642
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:05,600
Then you should know Petch was shot.

643
00:47:09,280 --> 00:47:11,920
Luckily, Petch regained consciousness.

644
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:13,600
Otherwise,

645
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:16,920
you'd be charged as an accomplice
to attempted murder.

646
00:47:18,120 --> 00:47:20,760
What nonsense are you spewing?
Accomplice to attempted murder?

647
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:22,480
I told you I don't know anything.

648
00:47:23,280 --> 00:47:24,160
Mr. Rachen,

649
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:26,800
are you and Pakbung
here to pick a fight with me?

650
00:47:26,880 --> 00:47:28,960
Why do you hate me so much?

651
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:32,720
Why are you accusing me like this?
I've had enough!

652
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:35,960
Darin.

653
00:47:41,520 --> 00:47:43,760
We don't have any solid evidence
that Ms. Darin

654
00:47:43,840 --> 00:47:45,760
worked with Rut.

655
00:47:46,400 --> 00:47:48,320
Do you think Trai won't believe us?

656
00:47:49,480 --> 00:47:50,520
Pakbung,

657
00:47:51,720 --> 00:47:53,640
Trai's not stupid.

658
00:47:56,880 --> 00:47:57,720
Come on.

659
00:48:00,360 --> 00:48:03,080
Pakbung, what's wrong?

660
00:48:04,600 --> 00:48:05,600
Does it hurt?

661
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:14,640
It's swollen. Does Trai know about this?

662
00:48:16,680 --> 00:48:18,440
He already took me to the hospital.

663
00:48:19,120 --> 00:48:20,360
Pakbung,

664
00:48:20,440 --> 00:48:22,880
that's not what I asked.

665
00:48:22,960 --> 00:48:25,680
I asked whether Trai knows
your ankle is injured too.

666
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:28,920
Just the cuts and bruises
on my face and body

667
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:31,640
already make him feel terrible.

668
00:48:32,840 --> 00:48:34,400
If he knew about my leg too,

669
00:48:35,360 --> 00:48:37,160
he'd never stop blaming himself.

670
00:48:37,800 --> 00:48:38,920
Pakbung,

671
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:42,920
you care about Trai so much
that you don't care about yourself?

672
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:45,920
If Mr. Trai's upset, I'm upset too.

673
00:48:46,680 --> 00:48:49,840
So please do this for me.

674
00:48:50,400 --> 00:48:51,960
Don't tell Mr. Trai about this.

675
00:48:56,520 --> 00:48:57,880
So Rut was arrested?

676
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:05,200
What a shame.
I thought he'd be more capable than that.

677
00:49:05,760 --> 00:49:07,120
Please don't come in yet.

678
00:49:07,200 --> 00:49:09,480
- Trai.
- You can't come in yet.

679
00:49:09,560 --> 00:49:12,200
I won't waste time with pleasantries.
Where's your daughter?

680
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:16,360
This is a summons.

681
00:49:20,760 --> 00:49:23,240
It's for Miss Khemika ChairatIttanawong.

682
00:49:23,320 --> 00:49:26,000
We'll need to ask her
to come give a statement at the station.

683
00:49:32,520 --> 00:49:33,960
On what charge, exactly?

684
00:49:36,280 --> 00:49:37,120
Here.

685
00:49:39,800 --> 00:49:41,000
<i>You rotten pakbung.</i>

686
00:49:41,080 --> 00:49:43,200
- <i>Stop, please.</i>
- <i>Hey.</i>

687
00:49:43,280 --> 00:49:44,240
<i>Please stop.</i>

688
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:48,480
It's just kids fighting.

689
00:49:49,080 --> 00:49:51,040
Why blow it up into something so serious?

690
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:54,400
It's not just a fight.

691
00:49:54,480 --> 00:49:57,760
Miss Khemika may also be connected
to an attempted murder case.

692
00:49:58,400 --> 00:49:59,600
Attempted murder?

693
00:50:00,200 --> 00:50:03,520
Wow, really? Are you genuinely shocked
or just pretending?

694
00:50:05,040 --> 00:50:07,440
You usually know everything,

695
00:50:07,520 --> 00:50:10,800
but this time, you didn't know
what your daughter did?

696
00:50:12,840 --> 00:50:14,760
Do you think
something this small can touch me?

697
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:17,600
Watch yourself.

698
00:50:17,680 --> 00:50:20,080
Oh, of course.
But don't waste your threats on me.

699
00:50:20,160 --> 00:50:22,200
Use your time and energy

700
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:24,360
to deal
with your precious daughter instead…

701
00:50:27,960 --> 00:50:28,880
if you even can.

702
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:46,120
Mom.

703
00:50:47,240 --> 00:50:51,040
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?
You wanna party with me, right?

704
00:50:51,120 --> 00:50:52,440
Party! Party! Let's dance.

705
00:50:52,520 --> 00:50:54,320
- Dance, dance.
- Mika. Mika.

706
00:50:54,400 --> 00:50:56,120
Get a grip.

707
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:58,480
What trouble did you cause?
Why didn't you tell me?

708
00:51:00,080 --> 00:51:03,000
I didn't want to tell you.
I wanted to slap her.

709
00:51:03,080 --> 00:51:05,000
Slap her till she's dead.
Do you understand, Mom?

710
00:51:07,640 --> 00:51:10,040
- Take Mika home.
- I'm not going.

711
00:51:12,320 --> 00:51:13,680
- Hey, I said I'm not going!
- Come on, miss.

712
00:51:13,760 --> 00:51:14,920
- I said no.
- Go, Mika.

713
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:16,000
Let go!

714
00:51:20,760 --> 00:51:22,880
DUANGKHAE RUEANGWICHAN

715
00:51:22,960 --> 00:51:25,280
RAT RUEANGWICHAN

716
00:51:25,360 --> 00:51:29,120
It took me a long time to come
and apologize to you, Uncle.

717
00:51:29,200 --> 00:51:32,520
But I'm sorry for everything
that happened to your family.

718
00:51:34,120 --> 00:51:35,480
I'm sorry.

719
00:52:27,640 --> 00:52:29,040
Take it.

720
00:52:29,120 --> 00:52:30,600
Yeah.

721
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:44,440
Don't zone out, handsome guy.

722
00:52:45,600 --> 00:52:46,680
I'm hungry.

723
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:51,240
Feed me, please.

724
00:52:57,800 --> 00:53:00,440
What're you staring at? Toss it.

725
00:53:00,520 --> 00:53:02,200
Toss it again, please.

726
00:53:02,280 --> 00:53:04,120
I'm waiting.

727
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:13,400
That's not me. That's my friend.

728
00:53:13,480 --> 00:53:15,320
Wait, so which one is you then?

729
00:53:16,600 --> 00:53:18,000
That one.

730
00:53:20,080 --> 00:53:21,840
Throw it this way. Come on.

731
00:53:22,840 --> 00:53:24,120
Ah, toss it.

732
00:53:28,200 --> 00:53:29,240
Delicious!

733
00:53:30,960 --> 00:53:32,240
More, more, more.

734
00:53:37,680 --> 00:53:39,880
What did you season it with? Wait.

735
00:53:45,440 --> 00:53:46,680
Here.

736
00:53:47,560 --> 00:53:49,920
Put your regret,

737
00:53:50,000 --> 00:53:53,080
your sadness, your pain, into this.

738
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:57,040
Okay, now throw it.

739
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:01,680
Throw it. Throw it far, far away.

740
00:54:02,840 --> 00:54:04,560
Throw your bitterness

741
00:54:04,640 --> 00:54:06,600
into the water.

742
00:54:07,400 --> 00:54:09,280
Don't hold onto it.

743
00:54:09,360 --> 00:54:12,760
What if it gets moldy?
Your hand's gonna rot, you know.

744
00:54:15,120 --> 00:54:16,040
Throw it.

745
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:19,400
If I throw it, will I really feel better?

746
00:54:20,160 --> 00:54:21,280
No idea.

747
00:54:23,960 --> 00:54:25,200
But at least…

748
00:54:26,360 --> 00:54:27,960
we'll be full.

749
00:54:32,760 --> 00:54:34,920
Throw it. What are you waiting for?

750
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:37,040
Throw it already.

751
00:54:37,120 --> 00:54:38,640
Like that. Look.

752
00:54:38,720 --> 00:54:42,320
Far away! Go!

753
00:54:47,080 --> 00:54:50,320
Toss it up to the sky,
let it fall into the water. Yummy.

754
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:57,920
More, more, more.

755
00:55:18,200 --> 00:55:21,120
You're done feeding the fish.
Don't forget to feed the human too.

756
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:23,880
What do you want to eat?

757
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:26,880
- BBQ.
- BBQ.

758
00:55:27,720 --> 00:55:29,200
Hey.

759
00:55:29,280 --> 00:55:31,440
You're crazy. You read my mind.

760
00:55:33,240 --> 00:55:34,760
Then should we go now?

761
00:55:34,840 --> 00:55:35,960
I'll use the bathroom for a sec.
Wait here.

762
00:55:36,040 --> 00:55:37,760
- Alright?
- Yes, sir!

763
00:55:38,520 --> 00:55:39,400
I'll wait right here.

764
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:57,040
I put ointment on,
but the swelling still won't go down.

765
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:01,360
Pakbung, let's go.

766
00:56:02,840 --> 00:56:04,840
Wow. That was fast.

767
00:56:04,920 --> 00:56:06,360
Didn't want you waiting too long.

768
00:56:11,440 --> 00:56:13,400
- Did you wash your hands?
- Not yet.

769
00:56:14,600 --> 00:56:15,440
Hey? Oh?

770
00:56:15,520 --> 00:56:16,360
Kidding. I washed them.

771
00:56:21,640 --> 00:56:23,400
Why isn't she back yet?

772
00:56:31,720 --> 00:56:32,560
Pakbung.

773
00:56:35,280 --> 00:56:37,600
Weren't you with Trai?
Why are you back alone?

774
00:56:37,680 --> 00:56:38,920
Where is Trai?

775
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:41,920
I told him myself
he didn't need to walk me home.

776
00:56:45,160 --> 00:56:46,520
I bought something for you.

777
00:56:59,520 --> 00:57:00,360
Let me see your ankle.

778
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:03,240
Mr. Rachen?

779
00:57:04,120 --> 00:57:05,400
It's really swollen.

780
00:57:06,640 --> 00:57:08,360
Rachen, what are you doing?

781
00:57:09,480 --> 00:57:10,560
Mr. Trai…

782
00:57:14,200 --> 00:57:16,000
You forgot the food you bought for Kanah.

783
00:57:19,920 --> 00:57:20,840
Thank you.

784
00:57:21,520 --> 00:57:22,520
Why are you here? What's up?

785
00:57:22,600 --> 00:57:24,200
Didn't I tell you to take care of her?

786
00:57:24,800 --> 00:57:26,320
- I am taking care of her.
- You sure?

787
00:57:27,120 --> 00:57:28,720
Mr. Trai took great care of me.

788
00:57:29,240 --> 00:57:33,080
He took me to make merit, we ate,
full of blessings, full of food.

789
00:57:34,040 --> 00:57:35,760
So, who's protecting who here, exactly?

790
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:38,760
Wait, you're here
to catch me doing something wrong?

791
00:57:38,840 --> 00:57:39,880
Let me ask you something.

792
00:57:39,960 --> 00:57:41,640
You're with Pakbung,
but where's your mind?

793
00:57:41,720 --> 00:57:42,640
What are you talking about?

794
00:57:42,720 --> 00:57:44,280
You can't stop thinking about Rut.

795
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:47,840
You're obsessed with the past, and you
forget to care for the person beside you.

796
00:57:47,920 --> 00:57:49,440
You didn't take care of Pakbung at all.

797
00:57:51,120 --> 00:57:52,520
That's enough. Mr. Rachen.

798
00:57:53,600 --> 00:57:56,040
Mr. Trai, I'll walk you to the car.

799
00:57:57,600 --> 00:57:58,800
One second, Pakbung.

800
00:57:59,840 --> 00:58:01,240
- Pakbung.
- Pakbung.

801
00:58:02,880 --> 00:58:03,800
Are you okay?

802
00:58:06,720 --> 00:58:07,720
Come on.

803
00:58:15,040 --> 00:58:16,760
You're out of chances now, Trai.

804
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:34,720
Get out of my house!

805
00:58:35,280 --> 00:58:36,560
Get out!

806
00:58:36,640 --> 00:58:38,120
Can I come back and live here?

807
00:58:38,640 --> 00:58:42,000
I'll give you a lump sum,
enough for you to get back on your feet.

808
00:58:42,080 --> 00:58:44,040
But you have to move out of my house.

809
00:58:44,120 --> 00:58:46,840
If you're going to stab me in the back,
do it cleanly.

810
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:48,320
Don't let me catch you.

811
00:58:48,400 --> 00:58:51,040
But if we let this go,
Mrs. Mookmanee will gain even more power.

812
00:58:51,120 --> 00:58:54,280
If you all still let Mr. Trai
remain the majority shareholder,

813
00:58:54,360 --> 00:58:56,680
I will withdraw all my shares myself.

814
00:58:56,760 --> 00:58:58,000
You're still money hungry as always.

815
00:58:59,040 --> 00:59:00,120
I care about money,

816
00:59:00,720 --> 00:59:01,960
and you only care about yourself.

817
00:59:02,040 --> 00:59:03,680
We have nothing left to talk about.

818
00:59:03,760 --> 00:59:05,440
I want Trai to trust me,

819
00:59:05,520 --> 00:59:06,680
for us.

820
00:59:06,760 --> 00:59:09,520
He's a murderer,
but I can't do anything to him.

821
00:59:10,120 --> 00:59:11,240
It's really Rut.

822
00:59:11,320 --> 00:59:13,200
How did he get out of prison?

823
00:59:13,280 --> 00:59:14,840
I'm gonna kill you, Rut!

824
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:16,240
Let go!

825
00:59:17,240 --> 00:59:20,320
I'll consider you one of Tritot's sons

826
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:22,920
and your life's going to be ruined too.

827
01:00:10,680 --> 01:00:12,920
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
